# WMS API Authentication Testing
# Use this file to test the authentication endpoints

### Login with admin credentials
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### Login with manager credentials
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "manager",
  "password": "manager123"
}

### Get current user info (requires authentication)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Get all users (Admin/Manager only)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/users
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Register a new user (Admin/Manager only)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "username": "employee1",
  "password": "employee123",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "role": "Employee"
}

### Change password (authenticated users)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/change-password
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "currentPassword": "admin123",
  "newPassword": "newpassword123"
}

### Test protected warehouse endpoint
GET http://localhost:5000/api/warehouse
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Test creating warehouse (Admin/Manager only)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/warehouse
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Test Warehouse",
  "location": "Test Location",
  "description": "Test warehouse created via API"
}